title: Week 7 Rescheduled Games/ Weather Delays
text: Talk about it in Gridiron Talk It seems like the weather could be affecting another week of football, as some schools have moved up their games and have rescheduled.Please, if you have any updates on games in the state of North Carolina, please tweet to us at @NCPreps and @NCPrepsPOB.Continue to check back for more updates as we learn more information on the situation.(Courtesy of HighschoolOT, Charlotte Observer, 910 Preps, etc) Rescheduled Games: Gray's Creek @ Westover - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMLee County @ Douglas Byrd - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMLouisburg @ Warren County - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMOrange @ Northwood - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMOverhills @ Cape Fear - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMPine Forest @ Jack Britt - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMSeventy-First @ South View - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMSoutheast Raleigh @ Rolesville - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMSouthern Vance @ Bartlett Yancey - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMUnion Pines @ Terry Sanford - Moved to Thursday, 7:00 PMWest Columbus at South Columbus, Thu., 6:30 p.m.Fairmont at Whiteville, Thu., 7 p.m.West Bladen at Wallace-Rose Hill, Thu., 7 p.m.Word of God at Trinity Christian, Thu., 6:30 p.m.Lakewood at North Duplin, Thu., 7 p.m.East Columbus at Red Springs, Thu., 7 p.m.Northwest Guilford at Reidsville, 7 p.m. - ThursdaySoutheast Guilford at Ragsdale, 7pm - Monday FEATURED PRODUCT
